President Vladimir Putin of Russia signed the Act imposing administrative responsibility for violations of the terms and conditions of payment of goods (work, services) in procurement for public and municipal purposes.
The Act is designed to address the very acute problem of failure to fulfil its obligations by the contracting authorities in the conduct of public and municipal procurement.
Another two years ago, the situation in which entrepreneurs were unable to obtain payment under public and municipal contracts had been widespread.
At that time, the President of Russia ordered the Office of the Attorney General of the Russian Federation to take the issue for special control.
Because businessmen themselves could not deal with unfaithful customers who had made unfunded contracts, they tried to avoid the obligations they had made and included illegal conditions in contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, 9.7 thousand submissions have been submitted by the Public Prosecutor's Office to protect the rights of entrepreneurs and 4,500 officials have been brought to justice, 533 have been brought to the Office of the Public Prosecutor's Office and 75 files have been submitted to the Public Prosecutor's Office and 46 of them have been prosecuted.
As a result, more than 66 billion roubles were owed to entrepreneurs.
These enormous amounts have not been raised as a result of the non-payment of multibillion-dollar contracts.
Many, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs have resulted in more modest amounts.
This is a typical case.
The manager of a small company won a multimillion roubles social service competition.
Man has invested all of his working capital, has fully fulfilled his obligations, but the money he has not received in due course.
The result is an increasing financial comet of debts on salaries, taxes, loans that would lead to bankruptcy if the enterprise did not seek assistance from the Public Prosecutor ' s Office.
The problem has now been maximized in a number of regions.
However, as of the first half of 2017, the total public and municipal debt identified by prosecutors in the Russian Federation was around 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the Prosecutor ' s Office operates in manual anti-crisis management.
The Attorney-General personally conducts visiting meetings with local authorities, where all violations revealed by prosecutors and measures to address them immediately are dealt with in detail.
Such operational meetings were already held this year in Jaroslavla and Yekaterinburg.
The implementation of Federal Act No. 189-FZ, amending the Code of Administrative Offences to establish the administrative responsibility of the contracting authorities for breach of the terms and conditions of payment of goods (work, services) in the procurement of public and municipal needs, which was signed by the President of Russia last week, will be qualitatively improved.
The draft law was drafted by the Russian Ministry of Economic Development on the initiative of the Public Prosecutor ' s Office.
The new law will complement the Code of Administrative Offences article, which provides for a fine of 30,000 to 50,000 rubles for a violation by the employer ' s official of the time and order for payment of goods, works and services in public and municipal procurement.
If an official has already been subject to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the Russian Federation entities have already been instructed to ensure the implementation of these legislative novelties in practice.
