In Ukraine, Russian prisoners were offered to be sent to prison for illegal border crossings
The Supreme Council of Ukraine has registered a draft law under which the Republic may criminalize the Russians for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
According to the RT channel, a document registered in an electronic database of the Ukrainian Parliament entails a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to illegally enter the territory of the country.
It is noted that a term of imprisonment may be increased to five years for a re-infringement or a act committed by a group of persons.
If the offender was detained at the arms border, the detention time for him would increase to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had detained Ukrainians attempting to enter Russia outside the designated crossing points.
