In Russia, there will be two new territories for the ahead of socio-economic development, namely Abaza and Novatroick.
The relevant decisions of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, 4 August.
The boundaries and economic activities of TOR have been defined in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Hakassia.
There will be a special legal regime in the city of 15,000 people, as well as a minimum capital investment by residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
This is expected to attract some 2.5 billion roubles of investment to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
A list of economic activities in which the TOR “Abasa” will have a special legal regime for business activities, such as plantation, livestock production, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements for 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the Territory on the Abakan Mine City Enterprise.
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Hakasia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Mine-Development for the creation of the TOR.
Similarly, the authorities of the Orenburg region did.
There, the city of Novotroicki will also establish a territory ahead of socio-economic development.
This will diversify the monogeneous economy, reduce its dependence on the urban steel plant AO and create more than 2.3 000 jobs and attract more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will operate in the new TOR includes, inter alia, freshwater fisheries, food production, medicines and medical supplies.
Novotroick became the first of the Orenburg monogades to receive the status of TOR.
Let us recall that the pre-development territory is an economic zone with favourable tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges that are created to attract investment to improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for TOR residents are: a profit tax of not more than 5 per cent over the first five years, and at least 10 per cent over the next five years, a social contribution of 7.6 per cent over 10 years, a free customs zone regime, a concessional approach to the various infrastructure facilities, as well as a concession fee.
